cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper is about improving the efficiency and effectiveness of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for computer vision tasks, specifically image restoration. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel approach that combines wavelet transform with CNN architecture, which involves machine learning and signal processing techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the trade-off between receptive field size and computational efficiency, which is a common concern in deep learning, suggesting cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on various image restoration tasks, indicating cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a potential sub-category.
